.SH FISH 2.4B1 (RELEASED OCTOBER 18, 2016)
.SS Significant changes
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
The clipboard integration has been revamped with explicit bindings.
The killring commands no longer copy from, or paste to, the X11
clipboard \- use the new copy (\fBC\-x\fP) and paste (\fBC\-v\fP) bindings
instead. The clipboard is now available on OS X as well as systems
using X11 (e.g.\ Linux). (#3061 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3061>)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBhistory\fP uses subcommands (\fBhistory delete\fP) rather than options
(\fBhistory \-\-delete\fP) for its actions (#3367 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3367>). You can no longer
specify multiple actions via flags (e.g.,
\fBhistory \-\-delete \-\-save something\fP).
.IP \(bu 2
New \fBhistory\fP options have been added, including \fB\-\-max=n\fP to
limit the number of history entries, \fB\-\-show\-time\fP option to show
timestamps (#3175 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3175>, #3244 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3244>), and \fB\-\-null\fP to null terminate history
entries in the search output.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBhistory search\fP is now case\-insensitive by default (which also
affects \fBhistory delete\fP) (#3236 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3236>).
.IP \(bu 2
\fBhistory delete\fP now correctly handles multiline commands (#31 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/31>).
.IP \(bu 2
Vi\-style bindings no longer include all of the default emacs\-style
bindings; instead, they share some definitions (#3068 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3068>).
.IP \(bu 2
If there is no locale set in the environment, various known system
configuration files will be checked for a default. If no locale can
be found, \fBen_US\-UTF.8\fP will be used (#277 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:277>).
.IP \(bu 2
A number followed by a caret (e.g.\ \fB5^\fP) is no longer treated as a
redirection (#1873 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:1873>).
.IP \(bu 2
The \fB$version\fP special variable can be overwritten, so that it can
be used for other purposes if required.
.UNINDENT
.SS Notable fixes and improvements
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
The \fBfish_realpath\fP builtin has been renamed to \fBrealpath\fP and
made compatible with GNU \fBrealpath\fP when run without arguments
(#3400 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3400>). It is used only for systems without a \fBrealpath\fP or
\fBgrealpath\fP utility (#3374 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3374>).
.IP \(bu 2
Improved color handling on terminals/consoles with 8\-16 colors,
particularly the use of bright named color (#3176 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3176>, #3260 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3260>).
.IP \(bu 2
\fBfish_indent\fP can now read from files given as arguments, rather
than just standard input (#3037 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3037>).
.IP \(bu 2
Fuzzy tab completions behave in a less surprising manner (#3090 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3090>,
#3211 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3211>).
.IP \(bu 2
\fBjobs\fP should only print its header line once (#3127 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3127>).
.IP \(bu 2
Wildcards in redirections are highlighted appropriately (#2789 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:2789>).
.IP \(bu 2
Suggestions will be offered more often, like after removing
characters (#3069 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3069>).
.IP \(bu 2
\fBhistory \-\-merge\fP now correctly interleaves items in chronological
order (#2312 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:2312>).
.IP \(bu 2
Options for \fBfish_indent\fP have been aligned with the other binaries
\- in particular, \fB\-d\fP now means \fB\-\-debug\fP\&. The \fB\-\-dump\fP option
has been renamed to \fB\-\-dump\-parse\-tree\fP (#3191 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3191>).
.IP \(bu 2
The display of bindings in the Web\-based configuration has been
greatly improved (#3325 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:3325>), as has the rendering of prompts (#2924 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:2924>).
